{"key":"processedPost-11981643","value":{"id":11981643,"first":11981452,"last":11981772,"when":1265572229,"utime":"02/07/10 09:50 PM","content":"All you need is the PVC pipe and a bunch of fittings, a hack saw to cut it and some PVC cement to glue it together.&nbsp; What you'll need to do is measure your available space, and then just go to the hardware store and meditate on the fittings you see on the shelf.&nbsp; <br />Don't be embarrassed to pick up the fittings and hold them in the position you imagine gluing them later.&nbsp; The store clerk can't help you, so just tell him/her you're trying to figure out what you need, and you just need time to look at what's there and figure out your plan.<br />If you're like me, you'll probably come home with not enough to finish the job, and have to go back for the rest of what you forgot the first time.&nbsp;  Once you wrap the plastic around your frame, tie it in place with bailing wire or electrical twist ties.&nbsp; You'll have to punch holes in the plastic to tie it to the frame.&nbsp; I use a nail or my knife.<br />RR","title":"Re: pvc greenhouse build"}}